i have some worms in a cocoon eating my plants how do i get rid of them i used to have a nice japaneese red bush on the side of my house i noticed some cocoon looking things but decided to leave them alone i did and now they are multipluying and using the leaves on the bush to wrap themselves up in it they also go onto my evergreens and do much the same thing after i found out i started to pick them off and squish them bag them and throw them out the little worm like grubs are white and when i squished them the blood was green and kinda gross they are hard to pull of the branches and i would like to know what to use to get rid of them and possibly what they are called sounds like bagworms if they are still small like inch or less insecticide may do them in once they get bigger the insecticide is not as effective purchase some at your local nursery many kinds will do ask them for something for bagworms if they are larger picking them off and disposing of them is always good if you can reach them Silkworm Piccolo Junior Saga Gooseberry Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Blood (computer game) Monster Rancher monsters Red Hot Chili Peppers Creatures in Bionicle Malaria Tea 2000 Australian Grand Prix Salad Fingers Bedbug Spider Wood Biological pest control Tobacco Textile manufacturing Chao (Sonic the Hedgehog) Apple Insecticide Haibane Renmei Characters of Naruto Pine Pikmin series Carnivorous plant Christmas tree Japanese tea ceremony Aerial (dance move) Peanut Bonsai Skateboarding trick The Dalek Invasion of Earth Poker jargon Garfield The Inside Silk GunBound Chopsticks Timeline of alternative rock Naruto jutsu Drag racing Cranberry Gross domestic product Jackass: The Movie The Legend of Zelda series enemies Mosquito Nicotine Fast bowling Teen Girl Squad Big Bad Beetleborgs Professional wrestling match types Animal Professional wrestling throws Mushroom hunting Pachypodium key to species Bubble Bobble Professional wrestling attacks Gaucho (insecticide) Wil